\section{The Resonant Absorption Cross Section} 
\label{sec:III}
Here we derive the cross section for resonant absorption. As the width of the detector's 440.2 keV
level is much larger than the width of the thermally broadened axion profile, we must treat the
axion energy as a delta function while integrating over the broad nuclear level. Neglecting very small corrections due to nuclear target recoil, we find the cross section
\begin{equation}
    \sigma(\epsilon_a) = \frac{\pi}{q_a} |\mathcal{M}|^2 \, \frac{1}{\epsilon_a - E_\ex},
    \label{eq:cross}
\end{equation}
where the cross section increases linearly with the energy difference from resonance.
